OL,3,CStarmer 'stands by' decision not to
OL,4,Cget involved in initial Iran strikes
OL,6,FThe prime minister says he "stands by"
OL,7,Fhis decision not to get involved in
OL,8,Finitial US strikes on Iran, despite
OL,9,Fcriticism by US President Donald Trump.
OL,11,FSir Keir Starmer was addressing MPs on
OL,12,FMonday after the US and Israel
OL,13,Flaunched strikes on Iran over the
OL,14,Fweekend.
OL,16,FHe reiterated that the UK "was not
OL,17,Finvolved in initial strikes on Iran by
OL,18,Fthe US and Israel," and that the UK
OL,19,Fgovernment supports a "negotiated
OL,20,Fsettlement" in the country.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1772528658
OL,3,CStarmer 'stands by' decision not to
OL,4,Cget involved in initial Iran strikes
OL,6,F"President Trump has expressed his
OL,7,Fdisagreement with our decision not to
OL,8,Fget involved in the initial strikes,"
OL,9,Fhe told MPs.
OL,11,F"But it is my duty to judge what is in
OL,12,FBritain's national interest. That is
OL,13,Fwhat I've done, and I stand by it."
OL,15,FIn an interview with The Telegraph,
OL,16,Fpublished on Monday, Trump expressed
OL,17,Fhis frustration at Starmer's decision,
OL,18,Fsaying he was "very disappointed" the
OL,19,FPM didn't initially allow the use of
OL,20,FUK military bases as part of the
OL,21,Fattacks.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1772528658
OL,3,CStarmer 'stands by' decision not to
OL,4,Cget involved in initial Iran strikes
OL,6,FThe government announced its position
OL,7,Fhad changed on Sunday night, giving
OL,8,Fpermission for the US to use UK bases
OL,9,Fto strike Iranian missile sites.
OL,11,FStarmer stressed the action was
OL,12,F"defensive" and that the government
OL,13,Fwould not be joining any "offensive"
OL,14,Faction.
OL,16,FTrump also said Starmer "took far too
OL,17,Flong" to change his mind.
OL,26,@yD@EO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1772528658
OL,3,CStarmer 'stands by' decision not to
OL,4,Cget involved in initial Iran strikes
OL,6,F"That's probably never happened
OL,7,Fbetween our countries before," he
OL,8,Fsaid, adding: "It sounds like he was
OL,9,Fworried about the legality."
OL,11,FConservative leader Kemi Badenoch said
OL,12,Fher party "stands behind America
OL,13,Ftaking this necessary action against
OL,14,Fstate-sponsored terror", accusing the
OL,15,FPM of "dithering delay."
OL,17,F"Unbelievably, in his statement today,
OL,18,Fthe prime minister still cannot say
OL,19,Fwhether he backs the strikes or not.
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@^O]pD@OOUqD@\O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1772528658
OL,3,CStarmer 'stands by' decision not to
OL,4,Cget involved in initial Iran strikes
OL,6,F"Today, the president of the United
OL,7,FStates has taken the extraordinary
OL,8,Fstep of rebuking the prime minister
OL,9,Fpublicly, saying he took far too long
OL,10,Fto grant access," she said.
OL,12,FLiberal Democrat leader Ed Davey
OL,13,Faccused Starmer of making Britain
OL,14,F"less safe" when he "fails to stand up
OL,15,Fto Trump."
OL,17,FChair of the Foreign Affairs Committee
OL,18,FEmily Thornberry said the attack on
OL,19,FIran by the US and Israel was "ill-
OL,20,Fadvised, ill-judged and illegal."
OL,26,@{D@_OU|D@aO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
